==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[maga#Old English|maga]].

===Pronunciation===
*/mɔː/, /<tt>mO:</tt>/

===Noun===
'''maw'''

# ''(archaic)'' the [[stomach]], especially of an animal
#:'''1667''': So Death shall be deceav'd his glut, and with us two / Be forc'd to satisfie his Rav'nous '''Maw'''. &mdash; Milton, ''Paradise Lost,'' Book X
# the upper [[digestive tract]] (where food enters the body), especially the [[mouth]] and [[jaw]]s of a [[ravenous]] creature.
#:'''1818''': To save poor lambkins from the eagle's '''maw''' &mdash; Keats, ''Endymion''
# any great, [[insatiable]] or [[perilous]] [[opening]].

